Upgrading EBS Volume Types Lab

lsblk
 - command to list what storage is mounted on the volume

 mkfs -t ext4 /deb/xvdb
  	- create a file system on the storage device

  	Best Practice to Stop your EC2 instance and create a snapshot and you can change your volume type

  	You can change volume types by taking a snapshot and then using the snapshot to create a new volume

  	If you chane a volume on the fly you must wait for 6 hours before making another change

  	